# Marketing mockups (X / Twitter)

When you ship a **user-facing feature** to Zumelia, also update marketing assets:

1. **`src/lib/marketing-mockups.ts`** — add or update slide metadata (`id`, `title`, `feature`, `caption`, `hashtags`, `shippedAt`). Remove from `MOCKUP_BACKLOG` when done.
2. **`src/components/marketing/SocialMockups.tsx`** — add or update the phone UI mock component in `MOCKUP_UI`.
3. **`ZUMELIA-TWITTER-PLAN.md`** — add an entry under **Ongoing content** (mockup + caption reference by slide `id`).

Mockup page (local): `/marketing/mockups`

**Do not** ask for or use the user's login credentials for screenshots. Use mockups or fictional demo personas (`DEMO_PERSONAS` in `marketing-mockups.ts`).

When the user asks "what to post on Twitter/X", mix:
- **Text posts** from `ZUMELIA-TWITTER-PLAN.md`
- **Mockup posts** — screenshot from `/marketing/mockups` + caption from `MARKETING_MOCKUP_SLIDES`

Default weekly rhythm: alternate text ↔ mockup (see plan doc).
